==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Carburet
<hw>Car"bu*ret</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Carbon</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A carbide. See
<er>Carbide</er></def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Carburet</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Carburet
<hw>Car"bu*ret</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Carbureted</conjf> or <conjf>Carburetted</conjf> (<?/); <pos>p.
pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Carbureting</conjf> or
<conjf>Carburetting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To combine or to impregnate
with carbon, as by passing through or over a liquid hydrocarbon; to
carbonize or carburize.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By <qex>carbureting</qex> the gas you may use poorer coal.</q>
<rj><qau>Knight.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Carburetant</ent>⟦br⟧
